# Cursor Rules for Agent Memory

This project uses rules stored in `.cursor/rules/` directory.

Cursor automatically loads all `.mdc` files from `.cursor/rules/` - no additional configuration needed.

Rules are synced from `rules/` directory. To sync rules to any project:

**From any project directory:**

```bash
# Option 1: Using the wrapper script (easiest - add to PATH)
cd /path/to/your/project
sync-rules --auto-detect

# Option 2: Using the wrapper script directly
cd /path/to/your/project
/path/to/Memory/scripts/sync-rules.sh --auto-detect

# Option 3: Using tsx directly
cd /path/to/your/project
/path/to/Memory/node_modules/.bin/tsx /path/to/Memory/scripts/sync-rules.ts --auto-detect

# Option 4: From Memory project directory
cd /path/to/Memory
npm run sync-rules -- --auto-detect
```

Or specify the IDE explicitly:

```bash
sync-rules --ide cursor
```

The script automatically finds the Memory project root and syncs rules to the current working directory.

**To add the wrapper script to your PATH:**

```bash
# Add to ~/.zshrc or ~/.bashrc
export PATH="$PATH:/path/to/Memory/scripts"
```

For more information, see:
- `.cursor/rules/README.md` - Rule documentation
- `docs/rules-sync.md` - Rules sync guide



















